    <stitle>STEERABLE DRIVE AXLE END UNIT: FABCO - DISASSEMBLE - WHEEL SPINDLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0201103" svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>WHEEL SPINDLE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the hub and wheel bearings. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02011_4.xml" xrefid="hl0201102">HUB AND WHEEL BEARINGS</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the brake assembly. Refer to GROUP 04 - BRAKES in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual
                for procedures to remove the foundation brakes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the ten 5/8" locknuts which secure the spindle and the dust shield/brake spider
                assembly. Remove the spindle (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0201108">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0201108" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0201108" filename="../figg02/G0201108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Removing the Spindle</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <para>The axle shaft may now be withdrawn from the differential through the spindle yoke.</para>
    </svcproc>
